#!/usr/bin/env python3

“””

sync_sg.py

Reusable Python-only CLI for syncing AWS Security Groups from a source JSON export

into a target DR account/VPC.

Design assumptions:

- Source/Prod is always provided as an exported JSON file via –json-path
- Target/DR is always a live AWS account/VPC via CLI args
- Source and target accounts are expected to be different
- SG references are remapped by normalized name into target SG IDs
- Dry-run should be used first before live execution

Examples:

Dry run:

python sync_sg.py \

```
--json-path exports/prodA-sg-export.json \

--target-profile dr-profile \

--target-region us-east-2 \

--target-vpc-id vpc-0123456789abcdef0 \

--dry-run
```

Audit only:

python sync_sg.py \

```
--json-path exports/prodA-sg-export.json \

--target-profile dr-profile \

--target-region us-east-2 \

--target-vpc-id vpc-0123456789abcdef0 \

--report-only
```

Live run:

python sync_sg.py \

```
--json-path exports/prodA-sg-export.json \

--target-profile dr-profile \

--target-region us-east-2 \

--target-vpc-id vpc-0123456789abcdef0 \

--yes
```

